  m_Name: Level_10_Lamanai
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 10
  levelName: Lamanai
  location: Orange Walk, Belize
  levelDescription: "Lamanai (\u201CSubmerged Crocodile\u201D) stands out for its
    remarkably long occupation, spanning over 3,000 years\u2014from the earliest
    Maya farmers to the Spanish Colonial period. Its riverside location along the
    New River made it a vital trade and transport node, supporting agriculture, craft
    production, and interregional exchange. Lamanai\u2019s iconic mask-temples, copper
    bells, incense burners, and later Spanish mission ruins reveal a city that adapted
    through shifting eras, maintaining cultural identity even as new powers arrived.
    Few Maya cities demonstrate such endurance, complexity, and cultural continuity.\n\nBy
    the river\u2019s edge, Lamanai survived age after age, its temples witnessing
    every turning of Maya history"
  requiredStackHeight: 45
  oneStarScore: 2000
  twoStarScore: 3000
  threeStarScore: 4000
  swingSpeedMultiplier: 1.5
  swingAmplitudeMultiplier: 1.3
